        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 6:03PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 603 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Pinon, or 18 miles northwest of Pueblo, moving east at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fountain, Pinon, and Pueblo West.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
